cated rice balls (Pin`d`a).\n* It is indicated for chronic diseases such as Sarvaanga S`hosha (generalized edema), Vaatavyaadhi (vata disorders), and Aayaama (respiratory disorders).\n* The procedure involves preparing a decoction of medicinal herbs, mixing it with milk and cooked rice, and forming it into 8 Pin`d`a.\n* The Pin`d`a are dipped in a warm mixture of decoction and milk and applied to the patient's body in a specific sequence of postures.\n* Svedana is performed for 15 minutes in each posture, totaling 1 hour 45 minutes.\n* After Svedana, the Pin`d`a are opened, and the medicated rice is rubbed on the body.\n* The treatment is completed with a warm bath and oil massage."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "6c1bf958-1a44-4daf-a037-02f8ab7b41d9", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Proc_Pindasveda.html", "file_name": "Proc_Pindasveda.html", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 4901, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "1f5c67c86d8493a740851a2a479b19725173da87a46a56648482559182335472", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "Pin`d`a Sveda Shasht`ika S`haalee = a kind of rice characterized by quick growth (ripening in about 60 days) Pin`d`a = a roundish lump or mass of food (cooked rice etc.) Sveda = the act of sweating or perspiring. Indications: Pin`d`a Sveda is indicated in serious chronic diseases like o Sarvaanga S`hosha, o Vaatavyaadhi, o Aayaama, o Aakshepaka, o Sankocha, o Stambha, o Pakshavadha etc. (C.Chi.26, A.H.Su.17) (1.This procedure is described here considering Sarvaanga Svedana. {Body Fomentation} For Local fomentation changes should be made accordingly. 2. Proportion of the contents is taken approximately and can be changed as per need.) o Medicines (e.g. Balaa Mool`a {480 Gm.}) should be crushed and decoction should be prepared as per standard method of preparation & then filtered. (480 Gm of medicines + 7680 ml water --> 3840 ml of decoction.) o Half of this decoction (1920 ml.) + Equal amount of milk (1920 ml.) + Shasht`ika S`haalee [Rice] (Aprox.480 Gm.) should be mixed. o This mixture should be cooked on mild fire without letting it to burn or to get stuck to the cooking pot, by repeated stirring. o This semisolid medicated rice is divided into 8 parts. o Each part should be placed over 8 separate clean smooth cloth pieces. (Preferably cotton cloth of size 18 X 18 {Approx.}) o Each cloth piece is tied well so as to form rounded Pin`d`a in such a way that medicated rice may not leak and at the tying end some cloth end is left for holding the Pin`d`a. o The remaining half of the decoction (1920 ml.) should be mixed with another equal amount of milk. (1920 ml.) o This mixture should be kept in a wide mouth pot for easy accommodation of 3 Kg. of liquid mixture and 4 Pin`d`a. o Patient should sit on massage table (or in the Dron`ee) with his face towards east. o Medicated oil should be applied on the head of the patient followed by oleation of whole body systematically. o When Snehana procedure completed, the patient should lie down on his back on massage table. o Two massagers on each side of the body (Total 4 massagers) should perform Svedana systematically. One on the upper part of body from neck to lumbar region and the other on the lower part of the body from lumbar region up to the foot end. Similarly on the other side of the body. o The Svedana should be done in Anulomana Gati i.e. from above downwards. o The fifth attendant should help in keeping the fomentation liquid hot, heating the Pin`d`a by dipping in the liquid and assist the massagers by transferring the Pin`d`a. o The fomentation should be done with uniform pressure and temperature all over the body. o All the four massagers should work in synchronization. o The entire body is fomented in seven postures as follows: 1. Sitting with legs extended on 90 0 keeping the hands on the two sides. This posture is used specially for massaging the legs and the back. 2. Lying down on back for massage of the front part of the body. 3. Lying on the right side of the body. 4. Lying on back again. 5. Lying on left side of the body. 6. Lying down on back again. 7. Sitting with legs extended on 90 0 keeping the hands on the two sides again. o Svedana should be done for 15 minutes in each of the 7 postures. (Total-1 Hour 45 Min.) This time duration may be changed accordingly. Pas`hchaatkarma: o After completing the procedure the body is rubbed with hands for 5 minutes o The Pin`d`a are opened and the medicated rice should spread on the body and rubbed well. o Svedana Dravya is removed from the body with the help of Naarikela Patra (Leaves of coconut tree) o Then the body should be wiped off with oily piece of cloth and Ushn`a Seka should be given. o Bath should be given with lukewarm water.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "702b3236-10a7-4725-8e9d-e8c6c743deab": {"__data__": {"id_": "702b3236-10a7-4725-8e9d-e8c6c743deab", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Proc_Pizinchila.html", "file_name": "Proc_Pizinchila.html", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 4100, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "**Summary of Pizinchila (Ayurvedic Body Massage):**\n\nPizinchila is an Ayurvedic massage technique involving warm oil applied to the body using cotton cloths. It promotes overall health, strengthens the body, improves digestion, enhances complexion, and prevents aging.\n\n**Benefits:**\n\n* Maintains good health\n* Strengthens the body\n* Improves digestion and complexion\n* Stabilizes the senses\n* Prevents aging\n\n**Indications (Conditions Treated):**\n\n* Facial paralysis\n* Weak digestion\n* Accumulation of toxins\n* Diarrhea\n* Thirst\n* Fainting\n* Poisoning\n* Abdominal disorders\n* High fever\n\n**Suitable Patients:**\n\n* Individuals who have undergone Ayurvedic therapies like vomiting or purging\n* Pregnant women\n* Weak patients\n\n**Procedure:**\n\n* The patient sits facing east on a massage table.\n* A paste of Indian gooseberry (Amalaki) powder and water is applied to the forehead to protect from heat.\n* Four attendants apply warm oil to the body using cotton cloths, squeezing the oil from a height of 12 cm.\n* The oil is massaged gently over the entire body in seven postures:\n    * Sitting with legs extended\n    * Lying down on the back\n    * Lying on the right side\n    * Lying down on the back again\n    * Lying on the left side\n    * Lying down on the back again\n    * Sitting with legs extended\n* Each posture is massaged for 15 minutes, totaling 1 hour and 45 minutes.\n* The oil is removed using coconut leaves, and the body is wiped clean.\n* The Amalaki paste is removed, and a lukewarm bath is taken after 30 minutes.\n\n**Precautions:**\n\n* Avoid exposure to extreme temperatures after the massage."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "d84a1708-1026-4f70-9194-196d68556315", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Proc_Pizinchila.html", "file_name": "Proc_Pizinchila.html", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 4100, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "0da6fb1b4599391a069202d9ea2bb4c56cda7ba316590f582dcd3f08ad80ac9b", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "Pizinchila  o Vaatavyaadhi o External injury o Fracture o Pain o Pizinchila can be performed in healthy persons for maintenance of good health as Brihan`a. o It strengthens the body, improves Agni and complexion. o It gives stability to the Indriya. o It prevents ageing. o Diseases: Mukhasraava, Mandaagni, Aamavikaara, Pravaahikaa, Trishn`aa, Moorchchaa, Visharoga, Udara, Atisaara, Navajvara o Patients: Those patients, who have undergone Vamana, Virechana & Garbhin`ee, Durbala Rugn`a. o Dron`ee (or massage table) o Medicated oil (Approximately 1- 2 liters) o Cotton pieces etc. o Ideal time for this procedure is in morning. o In Greeshma, Varshaa, S`harada Ritu. o This procedure can be done for 30-120 Min. o According to Dosha time period is as follows: Vaata- up to 120 Min. Pitta- up to 60 Min. Kapha-up to 30 Min. o Pizinchila can be performed for 7/14/21/28 days depending on the status of Dosha and general condition of the patient. Procedure: o Patient should sit in the Dron`ee (or on massage table) with his face towards east. o Paste should be prepared with Aamalakee powder & water. This paste is kept at the anterior fontanel with the help of gauze piece to protect the patient from excessive heat generated in Pizinchila. o Patient is advised to lie down on the table. o Four attendants should perform this procedure at the same time. Two attendants on each side of the body should perform Pizinchila systematically. One on the upper part of body from neck to lumbar region and the other on the lower part of the body from lumbar region up to the foot end. Similarly, on the other side of the body. o Each attendant has a piece of cloth in his hand. o The cloth is dipped in warm oil and is then squeezed the cloth over the body of the patient, from the height of 12 cm. with mild massage. o This oil is collected and reused after warming it. o The fifth attendant should help in keeping the oil hot and assist the others by transferring the oil dipped cotton pieces. o This procedure should be done with uniform temperature and pressure all over the body. o All the four attendants should work in synchronization. o The entire body is fomented in seven postures as follows: o Sitting with legs extended on 90 0 keeping the hands on the two sides. This posture is used specially for massaging the legs and the back. o Lying down on back for massage of the front part of the body. o Lying on the right side of the body. o Lying on back again. o Lying on left side of the body. o Lying down on back again. o Sitting with legs extended on 90 0 keeping the hands on the two sides again. o Pizinchila should be done for 15 minutes in each of the 7 postures. (Total-1 Hour 45 Min.) This time duration may be changed according to the need of the disease. o Oil is removed from the body with the help of Naarikela Patra (Leaves of coconut tree) o Then the body should be wiped off with piece of cloth. o Aamalakee Paste should be removed. o Bath should be given with lukewarm water after half an hour. o Avoid exposure to sun, air, cold etc.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "e8ecac30-1871-4411-8bbc-0aead376682d": {"__data__": {"id_": "e8ecac30-1871-4411-8bbc-0aead376682d", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Proc_Raktamokshana_Siraavedha.html", "file_name": "Proc_Raktamokshana_Siraavedha.html", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 15203, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "This pa