02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "Fomentation is a treatment in Ayurveda where a heated stone slab is used to provide heat therapy. Before the treatment, the stone slab is heated with the burning bark of trees that help alleviate Vata (one of the three doshas in Ayurveda). The burnt bark is removed, and the stone is sprinkled with hot water. A blanket made of sheep wool is then placed over the stone. The patient is massaged with oil and then lies down on the prepared stone slab. A woolen blanket is placed over the patient to trap the heat. The patient should change sides frequently to ensure even distribution of heat. The treatment is continued until the desired effect is achieved."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "ef8d4eee-6525-4a9a-9135-71c8d68aa542", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/As`hmaghana Sveda.htm", "file_name": "As`hmaghana Sveda.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 1022, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "f2fb64693d51d9275a36ca12f98fc6511bfd8b4a7ff729ee977e54bbbd5b9fa1", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "Prakaara Paribhaashaa: Fomentation is administered by sleeping over a pre heated slab of stone. Poorvakarma (Prerequisites): Instrument checklist: A slab of stone of the measurement of an individual is heated with burning bark of Vaata alleviating trees. The burnt barks are removed and the stone should be sprinkled with hot water. This slab should be covered with blanket made of sheep wool. Patient preparation: Body massage Medicine preparation: Vaata alleviating drugs like Devadaaru etc. Pradhaanakarma: The patient should lie down over the previously prepared stone slab and should be covered with woollen blanket in such a way that he will receive the heat of steam coming from the stone slab. The patient should lay changing sides frequently till desired effect is achieved.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ce4caad4-ee9d-40b0-bc52-dd646567a61a": {"__data__": {"id_": "ce4caad4-ee9d-40b0-bc52-dd646567a61a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Avagaaha S`heeta.htm", "file_name": "Avagaaha S`heeta.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 838, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "Avagaaha is a procedure in Ayurveda medicine where the body or a part of it is immersed in a tube filled with a decoction to remove toxins (Visha). Cold decoctions are used for the procedure, while hot decoctions are used to treat symptoms like coldness of the limbs or body. The affected part or the entire body is immersed in the appropriate decoction for 48 minutes. This procedure helps in reducing circulation and promoting blood coagulation, ultimately relieving the symptoms of Vishavega (a condition caused by the accumulation of toxins in the body)."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "2c178f69-62ae-4c71-b7e8-5c90762d8725", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Av