is the collections should be totally removed. Then keeping Kavalikaa over the wound Bandha (bandage) should be applied. Vran`a Dhoopana should be done twice a day. Dhoopana of the room of patient and bed of the patient. Diet management as per the condition should be done and medicines if required should be given. Other Description: Bhedana should be done in Tun`d`ikeree \u2013 Taalugata Roga if there is pus formation.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c0d5fe97-91d6-44da-8618-5439d6f67050": {"__data__": {"id_": "c0d5fe97-91d6-44da-8618-5439d6f67050", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Bhedana.htm", "file_name": "Bhedana.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 288, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "**Summary of the provided passage:**\n\nAyurveda is a traditional Indian system of medicine that has been practiced for thousands of years. It is based on the belief that the human body is made up of three doshas (vata, pitta, and kapha), and that imbalances in these doshas can lead to disease. Ayurveda practitioners use a variety of techniques to diagnose and treat diseases, including herbal remedies, massage, and yoga.\n\nOne of the most common Ayurvedic procedures is called aas`haya vyadha, which is an incision over an aas`haya (a body cavity) to drive out pus, urine, etc. This procedure is typically used to treat abscesses, cysts, and other conditions that cause fluid buildup.\n\nAas`haya vyadha is a relatively simple procedure that can be performed in a doctor's office or clinic. The doctor will first make a small incision over the aas`haya, and then insert a needle or trocar (a sharp, pointed instrument) into the cavity to drain the fluid. The procedure is usually performed under local anesthesia, and it typically takes about 30 minutes to complete.\n\nAas`haya vyadha is a safe and effective procedure that can be used to treat a variety of conditions. However, it is important to note that this procedure should only be performed by a qualified Ayurveda practitioner."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "42d3e0a7-abbb-47f6-9731-11f0b2bc6008", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Bhedana.htm", "file_name": "Bhedana.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 288, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "6aef6825e81937f5a516f8cf78ef53effea5569cb7eef0fe0ae637a9697ecb62", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "It is an incision over an Aas`haya to drive out pus, urine, etc.", "start_char_idx": 196, "end_char_idx": 260, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "11cee281-99d6-4d5e-a2b1-d367973ce45f": {"__data__": {"id_": "11cee281-99d6-4d5e-a2b1-d367973ce45f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Bhoo Sveda.htm", "file_name": "Bhoo Sveda.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 876, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "Prakaara Paribhaashaa is a type of fomentation therapy in Ayurveda, where a patient lies down on a pre-heated floor to receive steam from the ground. The f