t should be performed twice daily, upon waking and after meals. The process involves using a stick made from specific trees, such as Khadira or Karanja, which are known for their bitter, pungent, or astringent properties. The stick should be about the thickness of your little finger, tender at the tip, and free of knots or cuts.\n\nTo prepare the stick for use, crush it with your teeth and hold the extracted juice in your mouth for a while before spitting it out. Repeat this process until a brush-like structure forms at the end of the stick. This brush can then be used to gently clean your teeth, taking care not to harm your gums.\n\nAyurvedic tooth brushing offers numerous benefits, including eliminating bad breath, removing sticky mucus from the mouth, freshening the breath, improving taste, and promoting a sense of well-being. It also helps remove plaque and keep your teeth clean and healthy."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "a3765080-851c-4dc7-ba16-03d32dce9615", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Danta Dhaavana.htm", "file_name": "Danta Dhaavana.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 1709, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "81e77da159b78f8f87689251d7a13517ab27fdec41393581c6e29abeb45b7cca", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "Prakaara Paribhaashaa: Brushing the teeth is termed as Danta Dhaavana. It should be done immediately after getting up in the morning and after food intake. Poorvakarma (Prerequisites): Medicine preparation: Arka, Nyagrodha, Khadira, Karanja, Kakubha, Madhu, Vyosha Pradhaanakarma The drugs should be bitter, pungent or astringent in taste. The stick of the stem of diameter equal to the little finger should be chosen. The stick should have a tender point. The stick should be of length equal to 12 Angula. The stick should not have any nodules or cuts. The stick should be crushed with teeth and the extracted juice should be held in mouth for some time and then spitted out. This should be continued till a brush like structure is formed at the edge of the stick. This brush should be then used to brush the teeth. If a powder is to be used for brushing then it should be very fine. Gums should not be harmed or damaged while brushing. Chikitsaa Karma (Benefits): Danta Daurgandhyahara (relief from foul smell of teeth) Kapha Apakarshan`a ( cleansing the mouth by removing the sticky mucous) Mukha Vais`hadyakara (mouth freshener) Ruchikara (improved sense of taste) Saumanasyakara (imparting a sense of well being) Danta Malaghna (Cleanses the teeth)", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "45f841ad-ec89-4741-b71f-2a7ad9286bd0": {"__data__": {"id_": "45f841ad-ec89-4741-b71f-2a7ad9286bd0", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Dhaaraa Sveda.htm", "file_name": "Dhaaraa Sveda.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 1006, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "Dhaaraa Sveda is a type of fomentation therapy in Ayurveda where a continuous stream of medicated liquid is poured over the body from a height of 12 Angula (approximately 24 cm). The duration of the fomentation varies depending on the patient's condition: 2 and a half Muhoorta (approximately 50 minutes) for dry and Vata-Pitta dominant conditions, 1 and a quarter Muhoorta (approximately 25 minutes) for Kapha dominant conditions, and until adequate sweating occurs otherwise. After the fomentation, the patient should rest, receive a gentle massage, and take a hot water bath. Medicated water with coriander (Dhaanyaka), buttermilk with Trikatu (a combination of ginger, black pepper, and long pepper), and soup with ghee can be consumed to enhance the therapeutic effects of the treatment."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "1e9d3a41-3fc2-4d96-8f39-d9247989bccc", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Dhaaraa Sveda.htm", "file_name": "Dhaaraa Sveda.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 1006, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "c1864f08e9df9ea8d4011f97d21ceb406707033b59d5a1f1d17bbc33b8b66198", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "Prakaara Paribhaashaa: The fomentation done with the help of a continuous stream of medicine is termed as Dhaaraa Sveda. Pradhaanakarma: The Dhaaraa should be done from a level of 12 Angula above the body of the patient. If the patient\u2019s body parts are very dry and if there is dominance of Vaata along with Pitta then the fomentation should be done for 2 and \u00bd Muhoorta. In case of Snigdha Kapha dominance the fomentation should be done for 1 and \u00bc Muhoorta. Otherwise the fomentation should be stopped after adequate sweating occurs. Pas`hchaatkarma: The patient should rest for a while. Gentle massage should be applied. Hot water bath should be given. Water medicated with Dhaanyaka or buttermilk added with Trikat`u and Yoosha added with ghee should be consumed.", "star