re also used. This type of fomentation falls under the Baashpa type of Sveda."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "57f65a86-a4c0-4c4e-8bf3-b790868f7906", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Naad`ee Sveda.htm", "file_name": "Naad`ee Sveda.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 1251, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "1280d063ddab3d11aaf586d8e2c5b22d553cfcdd20380b11a5d7bb64994a8ff1", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "Chikitsaa Prakaara: Naad`ee Sveda Prakaara Paribhaasha: Fomentation administered with the help of steam coming out of tube. Poorvakarma (Prerequisites): Instrument checklist: A tube should be prepared using S`hares`hika or leaves of Vams`ha, Karanja, Arka. The fore part of the tube must be in the shape of elephant trunk. The tube should be one Vyaama or half Vyaama long. It should have circumference of \u00bcth Vyaama at the proximal end and 1/8th Vyaama at the distal end. The tube should have 2 or 3 curves. This tube should be attached to a Kumbha (pot) containing decoction of prescribed drugs. Patient preparation: Body massage with Vaata alleviating unctuous drugs. Medicine preparation: Roots, fruits, leaves, buds, etc; flesh and head of Mriga, S`hakuna, goat etc. animals having thermogenic tendency. Mixed with Amla, Lavan`a and unctuous drugs, Mootra, Ksheera, midriff of Varaaha, Pitta, Asrik, meat of Graamya, Audaka and Aanoopa animals, Basta S`hira, Tila, Tan`d`ula. Other Description: This can be included under Baashpa type of Sveda.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "d14a04c3-cadb-46a3-9cc7-d412d0b5966c": {"__data__": {"id_": "d14a04c3-cadb-46a3-9cc7-d412d0b5966c", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Naavana Nasya.htm", "file_name": "Naavana Nasya.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 1690, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "**Summary of Ayurveda Nasya**\n\nNasya is a type of Ayurvedic treatment where medicated oil is instilled into the nostrils. The type of Nasya performed depends on the dosha (imbalance) being treated.\n\n* **Pittja Vyaadhi (Pitta imbalance):** Nasya should be administered in the forenoon.\n* **Kaphaja Vyaadhi (Kapha imbalance):** Nasya should be administered in the morning.\n* **Vaataja Vyaadhi (Vata imbalance):** Nasya should be administered in the evening.\n\nAs a **preventive measure**, Nasya can be administered:\n\n* During the cold season in the afternoon\n* During the Sharada season (autumn) in the morning\n* During the Varsha season (rainy season) when the sky is clear\n* During the Greeshma season (summer) in the evening\n\n**Types of Nasya**\n\n* **Snehana Nasya:** Uses medicated oil to strengthen the body and is indicated for Vataja and Pittaja imbalances.\n* **Shodhana Nasya:** Expels vitiated doshas from the body and is indicated for Kaphaja imbalances.\n\n**Dosage**\n\nThe dosage of Nasya depends on the individual's condition:\n\n* **Heena Maatraa:** 8 drops in each nostril\n* **Madhyama Maatraa:** 16 drops in each nostril\n* **Uttama Maatraa:** 32 drops in each nostril\n\n**Administration**\n\nThe medicated oil should be warmed to around 40 degrees Celsius and then instilled into the nostrils using a cotton swab."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name",