 eye health.\n\n- **Relief from roughness of feet**: It helps soften rough and dry skin on the feet.\n\n- **Relief from feet stiffness**: It reduces stiffness and discomfort in the feet.\n\n- **Relief from dryness of feet**: It moisturizes and hydrates dry feet, preventing cracking and discomfort."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "aa901949-6574-425b-a49f-307fdad0f4cf", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Paadaabhyanga.htm", "file_name": "Paadaabhyanga.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 858, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "ce490d4a923685e2015327ee7aa4b3c18922af7625eca10999315a3673921918", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "Prakaara Paribhaashaa: Application of oil massage to the feet is termed as Paadaabhyanga. This should be done as a daily regime for Svasthavrittakara (maintaining health) . Chikitsa Karma (Benefits): S`hramahara (relief from fatigue) Paada Sthairya (firmness to feet) Paada Saukumaarya (delicate skin of feet / softness of feet) Paada Balya (improves strength of feet) Drist`ee Prasaadana, Chakshushya (promotes vision) Paada Kharatvahara (relief from roughness of feet) Paada Stabdhataahara (relief from feet stiffness) Paada Raukshyahara (relief from dryness of feet)", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "4ebcb829-6be7-478b-8dd7-25fdaf74eb65": {"__data__": {"id_": "4ebcb829-6be7-478b-8dd7-25fdaf74eb65", "embedding": null, "me