aata should be done. The person who is going to do Paadaaghaata should have clean, soft feet with no cracks. He should be competent. Pas`hchaatkarma: Bath with warm water or decoction. Other Description: This procedure is very common in southern India.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "22c07c3c-a4e4-4403-87fa-dd3206bb6c2b": {"__data__": {"id_": "22c07c3c-a4e4-4403-87fa-dd3206bb6c2b", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Paan`d`ukarma.htm", "file_name": "Paan`d`ukarma.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 604, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "Paan`d`ukarma is a procedure that aims to restore the skin's natural color after a wound has healed and left a black scar. It is typically performed on fair-skinned individuals. The exact process and formulations used in Paan`d`ukarma vary, but you can find more information through the Anveshak search facility."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "31fd1c9b-5d53-46b2-ba1d-1d1451d33d79", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Paan`d`ukarma.htm", "file_name": "Paan`d`ukarma.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 604, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "091f03148d1eb99c8e1b4b579138ead6d40d70afaeef148b84b2923d0aad2c03", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInf