lty tastes, and hot potency. However, it's important to avoid using Kshaara Dravya (alkaline substances) as a follow-up treatment for Nasya (nasal medication) if the patient has mouth ulcers. Additionally, Gandusha is not recommended for children under five years old."}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["tag", "file_path", "file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e1bd1cd5-64b0-4b4c-b72c-49bb3f0dace6", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/S`hodhana Gan`d`oosha.htm", "file_name": "S`hodhana Gan`d`oosha.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 694, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15"}, "hash": "89372a6cdc87763e61064a023d8777656175d4f20e95c3dcfc9a6afd4b8db2f7", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "text": "Prakaara Paribhaashaa: The type of Gan`d`oosha used for S`hodhana (purification) of mouth and breath is termed as S`hodhana Gan`d`oosha. Other Description: The drugs used for this type of gargling should have bitter, pungent, sour and salty taste and hot potency. Gargling with Kshaara Dravya as a Pas`hchaat Karma of Nasya should be avoided if the patient is suffering with Mukhapaaka (ulcerations inside oral cavity) Gan`d`oosha is contraindicated in children below the age of 5 years.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c50e19de-79ed-4530-ba06-b5a62ec77b8b": {"__data__": {"id_": "c50e19de-79ed-4530-ba06-b5a62ec77b8b", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedu