 rough properties. It is important to scrape the wound adequately, but not excessively, and to remove all the dead or damaged tissue. The procedure is included in the Shasht`i Upakrama of Vran`a, which is a set of 60 treatments for wounds mentioned by Sus`hruta, and is also considered one of the Pradhaana S`hastra Karma, or primary surgical procedures."}}, "ebaf5601-04c6-4bbb-84f8-cc57b8a25fa2": {"node_ids": ["1eb30b95-6d40-4663-ad19-4fe083b0803e"], "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Vran`a Ropan`a.htm", "file_name": "Vran`a Ropan`a.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 1183, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "Ayurveda, a holistic healing system developed in ancient India, emphasizes the body's natural ability to heal itself. When a wound occurs, the body initiates a natural healing process. However, sometimes, additional stimulation is required to accelerate healing. In such cases, specific herbal preparations from Ambasthaadi Gan and Priyangvaadi Gan are used based on the wound's nature. These preparations are applied as powders, pastes, or medicated oils to promote healing."}}, "4b428a95-f4fe-466e-b44f-4b0323db4a3c": {"node_ids": ["7497c775-6993-45db-ba61-d443ccbd9737"], "metadata": {"tag": "p", "file_path": "/home/dai/rag/data/clean_html/Therapeutic_Procedures/Procedure_Files/Vran`a S`hodhana.htm", "file_name": "Vran`a S`hodhana.htm", "file_type": "text/html", "file_size": 1806, "creation_date": "2024-02-15", "last_modified_date": "2024-02-14", "last_accessed_date": "2024-02-15", "summary": "Vran`a S`hodhana refers to the process of removing remaining Dusht`a Dosha (vitiated bodily humors) from the skin or deeper tissues after Bhedana (surgical incision). It is performed using specific substances (S`hodhana Dravya) based on the nature of the Dosha and body location. These substances can include powders (A